definition: to be born/to give birth/life/to grow/raw/uncooked/student
to come/to arrive/to come round/ever since/next

sentences.english: Like Stephen, I tend to be somewhat contrary by nature.
sentences.chinese: 像斯蒂芬一样，我也是生来倾向逆向思考。

sentences.english: Do you feel like you were born to accomplish a special mission in life?
sentences.chinese: 你是否觉得生来是为了要完成一件生命中的特殊使命？

sentences.english: Strength alone knows conficts, weakness is below even defeat , and is born vanquished.
sentences.chinese: 弱者甚至连失败都不够资格，而是生来就是被征服的。

sentences.english: Forster was a venturer by nature.
sentences.chinese: 福尔斯特生来是一位冒险家。

sentences.english: The critic was born with a good memory.
sentences.chinese: 那个评论家生来就记性好。

sentences.english: Born- fu said that in order to diagnosis required for beautiful woman undress.
sentences.chinese: 生来福说为了诊断所需，要求漂亮的女病人脱衣服。

sentences.english: If you haudio-videoe finished dinner I'll ask over the waiter for the payments.
sentences.chinese: 借使你吃完了，我就叫办事生来算账。

sentences.english: You were born knowing your limitlessness.
sentences.chinese: 你生来就知道自己的无限。

sentences.english: Women are born with all of the eggs they will ever carry.
sentences.chinese: 女性生来就具有她们所要携带的所有卵子细胞。

sentences.english: Comrade Savitskaya was, simply, born to be a cosmonaut.
sentences.chinese: 萨维茨卡娅同志生来简直就是要成为宇航员。

sentences.english: I am favored with excellent sight.
sentences.chinese: 我生来就有极隹的视力。

sentences.english: Pearl was a born outcast of the infantile world.
sentences.chinese: 珠儿生来便是那婴孩天地的弃儿。

sentences.english: They are born without moral patrimony.
sentences.chinese: 生来便缺乏道德的遗产。

sentences.english: She can sweet-talk me into doing just about anything she wants me to do.
sentences.chinese: 你可知道，我想我那最小的女儿生来就是嘴巴甜的。

sentences.english: When Westies are born the ears are very small and stand up.
sentences.chinese: 当衣装生来耳朵非常小而站立起来。

definition: to foreordain/to be bound to/to be destined to/to be doomed to/inevitably
to be born with/to be gifted with
